  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failing inputs: it systematically characterizes where and how failures occur (e.g., by classifying error types in a case study, measuring which metamorphic transformations and guidance criteria produce more failures, and reporting diversity and iteration-based failure patterns). These analyses provide partial diagnostic insight (statistical/pattern-level) about failure distribution and symptoms. However, the paper does not trace those failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., corrupted/biased training data, spurious features, overfitting) nor analyze model internals (neuron activations, attention patterns, etc.) to explain root causes. Therefore the appropriate rating is Medium.",
